To encourage wellness, former Big Brother Naija housemate, Ekemeni Ekerette (popularly known as Kemen), has unveiled a state-of-the-art gym, Pure Fitness Africa. During the unveiling in Lagos, the celebrity Chief Executive Officer (CEO) said the centre, formerly known as Fitness Central, is different from the average gym. According to him, the facility boasts of top-of-the-line equipment and facilities, including a fully equipped weightlifting area, cardio machines and a group exercise studio. While assuring Nigerians of unique fitness experience, Ekerette observed: “I am excited to bring my passion for fitness to Pure Fitness Africa and help people transform their bodies and lives. “The goal is to create a welcoming and supportive environment where people feel inspired and motivated to push their limits and achieve their goals.” The fitness coach has trained several individuals with focus on functional training and personalised coaching that ensures that every member receives the attention and guidance he or she needs to reach his or her full potential. He added: Pure Fitness Africa also offers a range of classes, including yoga, dance and boxing. The gym’s vibrant and energetic atmosphere, innovative course and personalised coaching create fun and practical experience.” The ceremony, powered by Amstel Malta Ultra, was graced by business executives and top fitness and lifestyle enthusiasts, including Amaechi Okobi; Nancy Isime; ex-BBNaija housemates, Praize, Dotun, Wathoni and Alex Unusual, among others.